reviews.text: The people of this place are just into money making business. I wasn’t knowing they charge 150 bucks as Entry fees which is general entry and 250 bucks for Special entry. I felt like they are more interested in the money than the real prayers. After paying the entry fees they gave me a ticket were few programs were mentioned. After entering, few stops are there where you need to show the tickets and do particular prayings where also the donation boxes were there. You need not to give any donation there out of your will. Yes, if you are willing to then you go ahead. I went in afternoon so the floors were quit hot and because my footwear was kept outside it was very uneasy to walk in few areas. So I suggest better go either in morning time or  in evenings. Anyway the statue of Lord Shiva was worth seeing. And that was the only part I liked after I entered. I would have loved the place if the temple people were not into business and more about holy rituals.

Temple of Lord Shiva. A huge statue of Lord Shiva siting in meditation position is been erect here. Just situated in well approachable location, focuses on all holy location of Lord Shiva and benefits of meditation. One can buy passes for various pooja and attraction.. At last can sit in front of Lord and feel all positive vibes around. Must visit place.

This is good place. But the entry ticket prices are different like 150rs and 250rs. There is a ticket for 50rs. Normal days 50rs ticket and 150rs does not make any difference. Overall good place to visit within city limit but ticket prices are high. Temple closes by 8pm. Peaceful place.

This is good for one time visiting. You will feel good here. However, most commercial temple in the Bangalore. Basically, this is not a temple. Beaware, ask the tickets Rs 50 for entry only. Otherwise they will give you Rs.150 per head. If you are going there for pray purpose.

This temple has turned more into a business than a place of worship. The priests aren't interested in talking/worshiping but offerings. The environment is hardly peaceful. As if the entry ticket of 250/ is not enough, they ask for more money at every stage.

First time there and the service was great.  The waitress was new but, I believe the owner, came out and made sure that everything was going smoothly and she knew what she was doing.  The basil seed drinks were a great find.   The food was also full of flavor and exactly what we wanted.  Very good!! We will definitely return!

This is some of the best cuisine I've had. I came here on a recommendation by family. The food was hot and tasted absolutely wonderful. The service was exceptional and had a very peaceful ambience. The owner consistently came and checked on my family and I. I definitely hope to come back, I left that night very full and content.
Very nice owner! The waiter was very understanding. We only had an hour before our bus departure and he made the whole dining super smooth and quick
Love this place. The lamb gyro is the absolute best I have had before. I have tried severest other dishes like the korma and have not been disappointed. The garlic nan bread is killer.
This was a bit out of the way as I was driving through the area, but I'm glad I stopped! We had great service, and large portions of delicious food. The restaurant was clean and well kept.
